@host = http://localhost:8080
# When running locally with `dotnet run`, use the port printed in the console (http://localhost:5182).

# 1) Log in, then copy the returned "token" into @token.
@token = PASTE_JWT_HERE
# 2) Create an order, then copy its "id" into @orderId.
@orderId = PASTE_ORDER_ID_HERE
# 3) Copy a product id from GET /products into @productId.
@productId = PASTE_PRODUCT_ID_HERE

### Log in as the seeded user -> returns a JWT
POST {{host}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "demo@shop.test",
  "password": "Passw0rd!"
}

### List products (paging + sorting: sortBy = name | price | stock | category | createdAt)
GET {{host}}/products?page=1&pageSize=5&sortBy=price&sortDir=desc

### Create an order with one or more line items and an optional coupon
POST {{host}}/orders
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "items": [
    { "productId": "{{productId}}", "quantity": 2 }
  ],
  "couponCode": "SAVE10"
}

### Get a single order (items + computed subtotal / discount / total)
GET {{host}}/orders/{{orderId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Update an order: replace items, swap the coupon, and place it
PUT {{host}}/orders/{{orderId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "items": [
    { "productId": "{{productId}}", "quantity": 1 }
  ],
  "couponCode": "FLAT15",
  "status": "Placed"
}

### Delete (soft-delete) an order
DELETE {{host}}/orders/{{orderId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
